snippet.title: Fate/EXTELLA: The Umbral Star - Launch Trailer (NINTENDO SWITCH)
snippet.description:
The Nintendo Switch version of Fate/EXTELLA arrives complete with over 30 previously-released paid DLC costumes along with an exclusive new Unshackled Bride outfit. The Nintendo Switch version is available via the Nintendo eShop and in retail stores £49.99/€59.99.

Fate/EXTELLA: The Umbral Star is the newest title of the long-running Fate series. The Holy Grail has summoned fan-favorite characters from the series, pitting them in high-speed combat against vast enemy armies. A captivating storyline from acclaimed scenario writer, Nasu Kinoko, pulls players into the frantic, large-scale action.
 
Key Features:
16 playable Servants including characters from Fate/EXTRA, Fate/stay night, Fate/Apocrypha, Fate/Grand Order and other Fate continuities! Different servants have unique, powerful fighting styles.
 
The first action game in the Fate series, Fate/EXTELLA allows players to engage in intense battles on the ground or in mid-air to annihilate enemy forces.
 
The Nintendo Switch™ version of the game will come loaded with over 30 previously-released paid DLC costumes as well as an exclusive new “Unshackled Bride” outfit for Nero Claudius.
 
Players can enjoy the action with the original Japanese voice-overs and English subtitles.
